cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is about aligning 3D point clouds produced by sensors, which is a common problem in robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses RGB-D cameras and 3D laser scanners, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses stochastic gradient descent, which is a common optimization technique in machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with point cloud registration, which is a common problem in computer graphics (cs.GR).
